@startuml
' @id(DOM-ARCH-DIFF)
' @desc(DOM-ARCH-DIFF, "The structured diff + invariant-check model over the architecture SoT (DOM-ARCH-SPEC). An ArchDiff partitions changes by entity and id: added/removed/changed components, decisions (incl. newly superseded), and constraints — semantic, not textual. An ArchViolation reports a broken OCL-ARCH-* invariant. Both are pure functions of two parsed specs (diff) or one spec + the model registry ids (check), so they are unit-testable without git or IO.")
title Architecture diff + check model (objective)

class ArchDiff {
  + addedComponents : List<Id>
  + removedComponents : List<Id>
  + changedComponents : List<Id>
  + addedDecisions : List<Id>
  + removedDecisions : List<Id>
  + changedDecisions : List<Id>
  + addedConstraints : List<Id>
  + removedConstraints : List<Id>
  + changedConstraints : List<Id>
  + isEmpty() : Boolean
}
class ArchViolation {
  + kind : ViolationKind
  + subject : Id
  + message : String
}
enum ViolationKind {
  DecisionMissingStatus
  SupersededMissingSuccessor
  ComponentRefUnresolved
}

ArchDiff ..> ArchitectureSpec : diff(base, head) of >
ArchViolation ..> ArchitectureSpec : check(spec, modelIds) of >
ArchViolation --> ViolationKind

note bottom of ArchViolation
  check() backs both `mdd arch status` (exits
  non-zero on any violation) and the WARNING-level
  OCL-ARCH-* rules folded into `mdd validate`:
  OCL-ARCH-DECISION-HAS-STATUS,
  OCL-ARCH-SUPERSEDE-LINKED,
  OCL-ARCH-COMPONENTS-IN-SYNC.
end note
@enduml
